Toyota has unveiled its new Urban Cruiser crossover in South Africa, taking an aim at the budget crossover market. It is the second product of the Toyota-Suzuki alliance, following the launch of the Starlet. The Urban Cruiser is powered by a 1.5-litre naturally-aspirated four-cylinder engine, delivering 77 kW of power and 138 Nm of torque. Buyers have the option of a 5-speed manual transmission or 4-speed automatic, reaching a top speed of 170 km/h. Fuel consumption is registered at a frugal 6.2 litres per 100km, while CO2 emissions fall within the 145 to 147 g/km range. The safety and security specifications include ABS and EBD, side protection beams, driver and passenger airbags and ISOFIX. An alarm and immobiliser system is also included on all models. <img class="size-full wp-image-473864 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/UrbanCruiser.jpg" alt="" width="1000" height="667" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/UrbanCruiser.jpg 1000w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/UrbanCruiser-300x200.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/UrbanCruiser-768x512.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> <img class="size-full wp-image-473866 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/UrbanCruiser1.jpg" alt="" width="1000" height="667" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/UrbanCruiser1.jpg 1000w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/UrbanCruiser1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/UrbanCruiser1-768x512.jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-473880" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/UrbanCruiser10.jpg" alt="" width="1000" height="667" sr